    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so exhausting. the doctors keep saying \"manage it\" or \"try this new med\" but they don't get it. they aren't the ones living in this hell. sometimes i look at the silence of the night and think how much easier it would be if i just didn't have to wake up to this again. if everything was just... still. does that even make sense? to want it to just stop?",
